-- China's Shanghai Composite Index Rebounds as Commodity Producers Advance
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-02T03:37:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/china-s-shanghai-composite-index-rebounds-as-commodity-producers-advance.html
China’s stocks rebounded after
brokerages boosted their allocations for the nation’s equities
and as speculation U.S. debt purchases will fuel inflation
spurred a rally for the nation’s commodity producers.  The Shanghai Composite Index advanced 0.3 percent to
3,061.74 at the 11:30 a.m. break, erasing a drop of as much as
0.8 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  